e established pattern and avoids polluting the backend namespace.\",\n19\t      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n20\t      \"evidence\": [\n21\t        \"src/greeting.py exists (prior fleet task output)\",\n22\t        \"tests/test_greeting.py:4 (sys.path.insert to src/)\",\n23\t        \"backend/inference/config.py (domain-specific EngineConfig dataclass, different purpose)\"\n24\t      ],\n25\t      \"uncertainty\": \"None significant. The task explicitly says src/config.py and the existing pattern supports it.\",\n26\t      \"decision_needed\": false\n27\t    },\n28\t    {\n29\t      \"question_id\": \"q3\",\n30\t      \"answer\": \"load_config() should remain independent of backend/server.py's pattern. The server.py module is a 4400-line monolith that reads env vars at module level (e.g., read_bool_env at line 339). The src/config.py module is in a separate directory hierarchy with no import relationship to backend/. The task description asks for a standalone config loader for APP_NAME/DEBUG/DATABASE_URL — not a refactor of server.py's config handling. Keeping them independent is the right call.\",\n31\t      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n32\t      \"evidence\": [\n33\t        \"backend/server.py:314-339 (read_bool_env defined and used at module level)\",\n34\t        \"backend/server.py:4390-4391 (os.environ.get for host/port)\",\n35\t        \"src/ and backend/ are separate directory trees with no cross-imports\"\n36\t      ],\n37\t      \"uncertainty\": \"Future work might want to unify config handling, but that's out of scope for this task.\",\n38\t      \"decision_needed\": false\n39\t    },\n40\t    {\n41\t      \"question_id\": \"q4\",\n42\t      \"answer\": \"Yes, DEBUG should be parsed as a boolean from string values. Use the same truthy set as backend/server.py's read_bool_env: case-insensitive '1', 'true', 'yes', 'on' → True; '0', 'false', 'no', 'off' → False; empty/missing → use default. This is a well-established pattern already in the codebase (server.py:314-324). W